EMAIL VALIDATION RULES REFERENCE

Rule Number	Rule Description	Status
Rule 1	Email ID should mandatorily have a '.' after @	IMPLEMENTED
Rule 2	Email ID should not be Junk value (e.g. abcd@, NA@, 1234@)	IMPLEMENTED
Rule 3	Email ID should mandatorily have '@' and '.'	IMPLEMENTED
Rule 4	Before @ can have combination of a-z,0-9,!#$%&'*+/.=?^_`{|}~-	IMPLEMENTED
Rule 5	Should not contain space	IMPLEMENTED
Rule 6	@ allowed only once in Email ID	IMPLEMENTED
Rule 7	First character of the email id cannot be any special character	IMPLEMENTED
Rule 8	Dots (.) cannot be at the beginning or end of usernames	IMPLEMENTED
Rule 9	Consecutive dots (.) not permitted	IMPLEMENTED
Rule 10	After @ we should not have immediate dot (.)	IMPLEMENTED
Rule 11	Domain should not have any special characters apart from Hyphen(-), underscore(_), dot(.)	IMPLEMENTED
Rule 12	Hyphen - in domain allowed, but not as first or last character	IMPLEMENTED
